hetoric and politics, we begin to see the everyday people working to reconcile their commitment to black identity with their belief in Republican principles. And at the end, we learn the importance of understanding both the meanings African Americans attach to racial identity and the political contexts in which those meanings are developed and expressed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitical activityzUnited States. 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and governmenty21st century. 0aAllegiancezUnited States. 0aIdentity politicszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aafrican american identity.  aafrican american issues.  aafrican american republican.  aafrican american.  aamerican politics.  ablack conservative.  ablack identity.  ablack republicans.  aconservative.  adaily life.  ademocrats.  afirst person.  apolitical behavior.  apolitical issues.  apolitical parties.  apost racial.  arace traitor.  arace.  aracial identity.  arepublican party.  atrue story.  auncle tom.  avoting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052029189840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965508423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965508/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY